race.description: Jr Richards & Sons Country Boosted Maiden Plate
race.comment: REDFORD RIVER (4) improved sharply last start when facing the starter for only the second time, beaten a long neck over 1280m at Muswellbrook after looming up to win in the run home. Only needs to hold that form to be too good for this moderate line-up. NORTHERN EXPOSURE (2) stepped up to this distance for the first time and did a good job to finish runner-up at Dubbo a fortnight ago. Very fit after two runs back from a spell and with a bit of luck from a tricky draw can figure in the finish again. Despite being winless in 13 runs HUTT STREET (1) was sent around at $2.15 last start but missed the placings over 1300m at Narromine. Has run out of chances but from the inside alley is a top three hope. COOL NANCZYE (11) has been going okay in weaker maidens than this. Gets in well after the claim and is worth including in exotics. PRIZUGA (3) is in the mix if he finds the form that saw him miss by a head over this trip at Orange two back.
